Fully Qualified Keys in Segments

When you create segments, Data Cloud adds key qualifier fields to table joins so that you can accurately identify, target, and analyze your customers.

We recommend that all calculated insights use key qualifier fields in table joins and as a Group By dimension. Using key qualifier fields ensures that the insights data is interpreted correctly when it’s used in segments. You can edit existing calculated insights to add key qualifier fields.

When a calculated insight is used in a segment, Data Cloud checks whether the calculated insight contains a key qualifier field in the Group By dimension. If it does, the fields are included in the table joins between the DMO in the calculated insight and other DMOs in the segment. If it doesn’t, Data Cloud doesn’t use the key qualifier field in the table join, so you can continue to use the calculated insights that were created before fully qualified keys were enabled in the org.

If a calculated insight is used in a dedicated container in the segment, the generated query doesn’t include the key qualifier field in table joins to the CI DMO. Therefore, you can use calculated insights that don’t have a key qualifier field as a dimension in dedicated containers in segments. However, if a single container references both a calculated insight and other DMOs, the generated query includes key qualifier fields in table joins to the CI DMOs. In this scenario, you can only use the calculated insights that contain key qualifier fields as a dimension. If a calculated insight doesn’t contain key qualifier fields as a dimension, the segment execution fails.
